<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Structures, WTF</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?slartybartfast">slartybartfast</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:40 a.m. 17/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Structures, WTF<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/solusek_ro.cgi?read=79" TARGET=_self>Structures, WTF</A> (Spelmyst)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>> Is it just me, or does anyone else feel that

<BR>&gt; a structure or building should protect you
<BR>&gt; from the outside world and environment? I
<BR>&gt; thought the whole point in creating houses
<BR>&gt; and building was to protect you. Am I the
<BR>&gt; only person getting tired of being attacked
<BR>&gt; or even killed through a wall by some,
<P>SNIP
<P>I completely agree, and YES Verant was notified of the 'attacking through doors' phenomenon. As I recall Verant's excuse to this problem was their statement of "we left it in because of game balance issues". Basically they probably couldn't fix it without some major rewrites of the collision routines and combat system (my guesstimate).
<P>This is another example of my experience of being attacked by a Fire Elemental out at sea, in the belly of a boat (which is somewhat underwater by the way). Does that make sense to you? You'd expect a fire elemental to fear water.. By the way, I never even saw him. He just kept pegging me through the hull, so I assume he was underwater.
<P>Another annoying bug is watching sharks and other sea life popping out of the water onto land, boats or what not. I once saw a GIANT shark pop up onto the deck of the boat, watched its jaws beging chomping and the next second the guy in front of me was dead. The Shark just sat there on the boat a while until it decided to 'disappear' back into the watery depths below.
<P>I wish I could do that.. i'd love to be able to kill beasties through dungeon walls and doors. It would make my life much easier wouldn't it?
<P>S
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
